CONGRESSMAN JOHN LEWIS: Good.

00:37:19.550 --> 00:37:20.511
AUDIENCE: Hello.

00:37:20.511 --> 00:37:21.260
Thanks for coming.

00:37:22.780 --> 00:37:25.760
My question is about
the forms of racism

00:37:25.760 --> 00:37:29.580
that are a little bit
more harder to detect,

00:37:29.580 --> 00:37:31.110
more insidious.

00:37:31.110 --> 00:37:33.220
So, I mean, there's
instances like Ferguson,

00:37:33.220 --> 00:37:36.940
which are like forms of violence
that we can physically see.

00:37:36.940 --> 00:37:40.440
But there seems to
be like a lot of I

00:37:40.440 --> 00:37:42.840
can call quote, unquote,
invisible racism,

00:37:42.840 --> 00:37:45.120
structural conditions or
economic stratification

00:37:45.120 --> 00:37:48.610
that makes life on certain
minorities very difficult.

00:37:48.610 --> 00:37:52.900
And so, how do things
like nonviolence,

00:37:52.900 --> 00:37:57.220
per se, actually prevent things
like structural blockages

00:37:57.220 --> 00:37:59.950
that prevent people from
voting in the first place?

00:37:59.950 --> 00:38:03.920
And how do people like
us who are privileged

00:38:03.920 --> 00:38:06.040
do something substantive
to actually help

00:38:06.040 --> 00:38:07.790
people who are
structurally disadvantaged?

00:38:09.417 --> 00:38:11.375
CONGRESSMAN JOHN LEWIS:
Well, you have a voice.

00:38:12.830 --> 00:38:13.570
You're smart.

00:38:13.570 --> 00:38:14.454
You have the ability.

00:38:14.454 --> 00:38:15.370
You have the capacity.

00:38:17.430 --> 00:38:19.840
You could use the
new technology.

00:38:19.840 --> 00:38:22.015
You could communicate.

00:38:23.480 --> 00:38:26.670
And you have to help
inform and educate people.

00:38:26.670 --> 00:38:30.700
When Martin Luther King, Junior,
would be preaching sometime

00:38:30.700 --> 00:38:34.727
in Atlanta at his
father's church later when

00:38:34.727 --> 00:38:36.660
they co-pastored, he
would be preaching,

00:38:36.660 --> 00:38:38.450
and his father would
say-- Daddy King,

00:38:38.450 --> 00:38:41.010
we called him-- would
say, "Make it plain, son.

00:38:41.010 --> 00:38:42.180
Make it plain."

00:38:42.180 --> 00:38:44.280
And he just kept
saying make it plain.

00:38:44.280 --> 00:38:47.090
I think you can
help make it plain.

00:38:47.090 --> 00:38:52.980
People like to hide stuff-- like
to hide it in the dark corner

00:38:52.980 --> 00:38:55.570
or some place under
the American rug.

00:38:55.570 --> 00:38:58.480
We have to help bring it out,
bring it out into the open

00:38:58.480 --> 00:38:59.660
into the light.

00:38:59.660 --> 00:39:06.150
So in a sense, why would members
of Congress and 200 citizens

00:39:06.150 --> 00:39:09.150
go and deliberating
court getting arrested?

00:39:10.530 --> 00:39:11.840
We want to put a face on it.

00:39:11.840 --> 00:39:13.730
We want to make it real.

00:39:13.730 --> 00:39:15.880
We want to send it to
the Speaker of the House.

00:39:15.880 --> 00:39:18.140
You bring this
bill to the floor.

00:39:18.140 --> 00:39:19.630
The Senate passed it.

00:39:19.630 --> 00:39:21.480
We have the votes to pass it.

00:39:21.480 --> 00:39:26.970
So you have to help put
the spotlight on it.

00:39:28.070 --> 00:39:30.100
And just one day
will not necessarily.

00:39:30.100 --> 00:39:32.800
I tell people all the time
that the struggle is not

00:39:32.800 --> 00:39:34.910
a struggle that
lasts for a few days

00:39:34.910 --> 00:39:36.800
or a few weeks or a few years.

00:39:36.800 --> 00:39:41.770
It is a struggle of a lifetime
to create what Dr. King called

00:39:41.770 --> 00:39:45.860
a beloved community or to create
an America community, a war

00:39:45.860 --> 00:39:47.325
community at peace with itself.

00:39:50.930 --> 00:39:51.640
Be creative.

00:39:51.640 --> 00:39:52.770
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:39:52.770 --> 00:39:54.186
CONGRESSMAN JOHN
LEWIS: Thank you.

00:39:56.992 --> 00:39:59.200
AUDIENCE: Just want to thank
you both for coming out.

