00:40:40.520 --> 00:40:43.250
Everyone is sort of
siloing themselves

00:40:43.250 --> 00:40:44.690
in a particular message.

00:40:44.690 --> 00:40:48.060
There was a lot of reports
about the difference

00:40:48.060 --> 00:40:49.790
in African American
responses to events

00:40:49.790 --> 00:40:51.540
at Ferguson versus
white responses.

00:40:51.540 --> 00:40:54.230
And one of the key insights
into that was well,

00:40:54.230 --> 00:40:57.953
the Caucasian Americans
mostly hang out

00:40:57.953 --> 00:41:00.490
with Caucasian Americans,
and therefore, only

00:41:00.490 --> 00:41:02.370
reinforce the views
that they already had.

00:41:02.370 --> 00:41:07.290
And so, with that being said,
how, even though the technology

00:41:07.290 --> 00:41:09.289
and opportunity
is there, it seems

00:41:09.289 --> 00:41:11.330
like it's being used for
the opposite of bringing

00:41:11.330 --> 00:41:12.204
the country together.

00:41:12.204 --> 00:41:13.670
It's used to pull people apart.

00:41:13.670 --> 00:41:17.050
So, sort of, how do we actually
go about fixing those gaps

00:41:17.050 --> 00:41:19.350
and those divides
given that everybody

00:41:19.350 --> 00:41:21.870
has the opportunity
and the source to a,

00:41:21.870 --> 00:41:24.700
find the true message, but
also listen to the message

00:41:24.700 --> 00:41:26.370
that they want to
hear and sort of try

00:41:26.370 --> 00:41:28.620
to reconcile both
of those facts.

00:41:29.599 --> 00:41:31.640
CONGRESSMAN JOHN LEWIS:
Well, I've said to Andrew

00:41:31.640 --> 00:41:34.100
and I've said to some of my
colleagues in the Congress

00:41:34.100 --> 00:41:37.390
from time to time, I've
said in the Congress we

00:41:37.390 --> 00:41:40.040
need to conduct some
nonviolent workshops.

00:41:40.040 --> 00:41:42.580
Just bring in members
of Congress together.

00:41:42.580 --> 00:41:45.420
Because the American people
think we're so divided,

00:41:45.420 --> 00:41:48.050
into a larger sense,
we are divided.

00:41:48.050 --> 00:41:50.620
So one of the things I've been
doing with an organization

00:41:50.620 --> 00:41:54.100
called Faith and Politics
for the past 15 years,

00:41:54.100 --> 00:41:58.600
taking members of Congress,
taking business executives,

00:41:58.600 --> 00:42:04.570
taking students and others,
to Selma, to Montgomery,

00:42:04.570 --> 00:42:07.910
to Birmingham, to meet
some of the people,

00:42:07.910 --> 00:42:09.690
to meet some of
the foot soldiers,

00:42:09.690 --> 00:42:13.180
to meet the family of the
four little girls that

00:42:13.180 --> 00:42:14.600
were bombed and killed.

00:42:15.720 --> 00:42:20.895
To go-- and you have people,
Southerners, black, white.

00:42:22.110 --> 00:42:26.995
You have people living in the
Midwest or the West Coast that

00:42:26.995 --> 00:42:29.650
have never traveled
in the South.

00:42:29.650 --> 00:42:32.280
And they go and walk
through these churches,

00:42:32.280 --> 00:42:34.740
through this historic
site, they meet people.

00:42:34.740 --> 00:42:36.190
And they'll change.

00:42:36.190 --> 00:42:43.860
Or to have someone who beat
you 50 years ago and then

00:42:43.860 --> 00:42:47.717
come up or come to your
office in Washington and say,

00:42:47.717 --> 00:42:48.550
you know, I'm sorry.

00:42:50.400 --> 00:42:51.670
I want to apologize.

00:42:51.670 --> 00:42:52.650
Will you forgive me?

00:42:53.750 --> 00:42:59.150
And to have a chief of police
in Montgomery, Alabama,

00:42:59.150 --> 00:43:02.130
almost two years ago,
but more than a year ago,

00:43:02.130 --> 00:43:04.430
a young guy who
was not even born,

00:43:04.430 --> 00:43:08.550
said to me, "Congressman,
when you came here in 1961,

00:43:08.550 --> 00:43:11.310
more than 50 years ago,
our police department

00:43:11.310 --> 00:43:13.790
was not kind to you
and your colleagues.

00:43:13.790 --> 00:43:15.320
We withdrew."

00:43:15.320 --> 00:43:16.710
He was not a police officer.

00:43:16.710 --> 00:43:17.950
He was not even born.

00:43:17.950 --> 00:43:19.720
But he said we withdrew.

00:43:19.720 --> 00:43:21.440
We let our angry mark beat you.

00:43:21.440 --> 00:43:23.630
He said, but our police
department today is better.

00:43:24.990 --> 00:43:27.412
Before anyone becomes a member
of this police department,

00:43:27.412 --> 00:43:28.870
they must know
something about what

00:43:28.870 --> 00:43:30.570
happened in Montgomery,
what happened

00:43:30.570 --> 00:43:32.960
in Selma, what
happened in Birmingham.

00:43:32.960 --> 00:43:33.890
He went on talking.

00:43:35.670 --> 00:43:37.320
This chief is white.

00:43:37.320 --> 00:43:38.830
His deputy is African American.

00:43:40.540 --> 00:43:41.960
The young deputy
didn't even know

00:43:41.960 --> 00:43:43.990
the chief was going
to go down that road.

00:43:43.990 --> 00:43:48.450
And then before it was over,
the chief said something like,

00:43:48.450 --> 00:43:51.350
"Congressman, because
of my admiration for you

00:43:51.350 --> 00:43:54.272
and your colleagues
of what you did,

00:43:54.272 --> 00:43:55.760
I'm going to take off my badge.

00:43:56.912 --> 00:43:58.980
I'm going to give it to you.

00:43:58.980 --> 00:44:01.430
I'm going to present
you my badge."

00:44:01.430 --> 00:44:02.880
That's what he said.

00:44:02.880 --> 00:44:06.030
And I said Chief,
you can't do that.

00:44:06.030 --> 00:44:07.350
You the Chief of Police.

00:44:07.350 --> 00:44:09.110
You need your badge.

00:44:09.110 --> 00:44:12.150
And the young African
American deputy lost it.

00:44:12.150 --> 00:44:13.850
He just started
crying, because he

00:44:13.850 --> 00:44:15.860
didn't know his chief
wasn't going to do that.

00:44:15.860 --> 00:44:20.060
And then the whole audience,
even members of Congress,

00:44:20.060 --> 00:44:23.720
Democrats and Republicans,
black and white, Latinos

00:44:23.720 --> 00:44:27.030
and Asian Americans, all
sitting there crying.

00:44:28.180 --> 00:44:30.910
So sometimes we
have to find ways.

00:44:30.910 --> 00:44:35.540
Sometimes it may not
intention, but it

00:44:35.540 --> 00:44:37.710
tends to reach people and
catch them in the gut.

00:44:39.670 --> 00:44:41.854
ANDREW AYDIN: And,
you know, that's not

00:44:41.854 --> 00:44:44.020
a question that wasn't asked
during the Civil Rights

00:44:44.020 --> 00:44:45.304
Movement.

00:44:45.304 --> 00:44:47.470
When Dr. King wrote a letter
from a Birmingham jail,

00:44:47.470 --> 00:44:49.120
there were whites in the
community who said, you know,

00:44:49.120 --> 00:44:50.230
why are you agitating now?

00:44:50.230 --> 00:44:51.270
Why are you doing this?

00:44:52.274 --> 00:44:54.440
And there were differing
perspectives based on race.

00:44:54.440 --> 00:44:56.080
But I think what
we need to do today

00:44:56.080 --> 00:44:57.830
is we need to look at
some of these issues

00:44:57.830 --> 00:45:02.100
